15/05/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Attending a conference in the Bulgarian capital Friday (13 May), Romanian Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu said that a safe and prosperous Black Sea region might strengthen the EU. During his speech at a forum entitled "Security in the Black Sea Area", Tariceanu said the region's strong economic potential could play a significant role in developing stable democracies there. The conference was held within the framework of the Liberal International Congress. Tariceanu participated as chairman of Romania's ruling National Liberal Party. (Rompres - 14/05/05)
